                <p>The sun data was collected by the Solar and Heliospheric Observatory. The spacecraft was launched in 1995 by NASA and ESA. The spacecraft has colled two datasets so far.<p>
                <ul class="span-6">
                  <li>The first dataset is 6 years of images spliced together to create a full coverage of the sun's surface</li>
                  <li>The second dataset is from October 2003. The spacecraft observed an X17.2 and X10 magnitude solar flare on October 29<sup>th</sup></li>
                </ul>
              <video src="http://www.renaissancesoftware.net/paulgrenning/oct_2003.mp4" controls="controls" class="media-in-slide span-10">Video tag not supported</video> 
